HEADWORD: Coadunation
<hw>Co*ad`u*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>coadunatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>Union, as in one body or mass;
unity.</def> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

